						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar of another rock-cut cave in the same hill.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅgachōḷadēva I: Year [2]2 = 1091-92 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Pugaḻmādu viḷaṅga,</hi> etc. of the king.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land on the southern outskirts of Kūnkuḷam as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḻāppuṟam</hi> (for festival purposes) to god Tirumalaiuḍaiya-nāyanār of Tirukkuṉṟakkuḍi by the villagers of Tirukkuṉṟakkuḍi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tenpugalūr. </p>						

						</summary>
